  "prompt": "What marks and rank is required to get Aerospace Engineering in IIT Bombay in JEE Advanced 2017?",
  "response": "To secure a seat in the Aerospace Engineering program at the Indian Institute of Technology (IIT) Bombay in 2017 through the JEE Advanced examination, a candidate typically needed to achieve a rank within the top few thousand, although exact ranks can vary from year to year based on the difficulty of the exam and the performance of the candidates. \n\nFor JEE Advanced 2017, the closing rank for Aerospace Engineering for the General category was approximately around 1335. It's important to note that cutoff ranks can vary for different categories due to reservation policies. Here's a rough idea of what was required:\n\n- **General Category**: Closing rank was around 1335.\n- **OBC-NCL Category**: Closing rank was around 725.\n- **SC Category**: Closing rank was around 297.\n- **ST Category**: Closing rank was around 156.\n\nThe exact marks corresponding to these ranks can be difficult to pinpoint as they depend on various factors such as the exam's overall difficulty and the distribution of scores, but typically, a rank within these ranges could have been achieved with marks well above the median score of that year. \n\nFor future candidates and accuracy, it is always advisable to check the latest cutoff trends and detailed data provided by the Joint Seat Allocation Authority (JoSAA) which conducts counseling for IIT admissions.",
